medical_history.chief_complaint: Worse diffuse abdominal pain and nausea.
medical_history.history_of_present_illness: Symptoms of diffuse abdominal pain started 12 hours ago, radiating to the back. Patient also had episodes of postprandial right upper quadrant pain radiating to her back that occurred previously and lasted for 25 minutes. Pain intensity has progressively worsened, particularly in the periumbilical area. Nausea and non-bilious, non-bloody emesis are also reported.
